        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing Elijah Noble, who represents the "Texas Emigrating Society" of Lexington.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Lexington </placeName><date when="1822-06-06">June 6th 1822</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>This will be handed you by <persName>Mr Noble</persName> of this place, his object in
visiting <placeName>Texas </placeName>is to settle provided the country pleases him, and he
can make a satisfactory arrangement with you <persName>Mr Noble</persName> was raised
by my <persName>father </persName>and his <persName>wife </persName>by my <persName>mother</persName>, they have a large <persName>family</persName>
of <persName>children</persName>. He is an industrious, persevering enterprising man and
a man of business If he should settle with you he will make a 
usefull and valuable citizen I feel much interested in his and his familys
future welfare and prosperity</p>

<p>Any attention it may be in your power to pay him, will be by me
acknowledged as a favour</p>

<p>When <persName>Mr Noble</persName> returns, write me a full description of your 
country, and be assured your letter shall not long remain unanswered</p>

<p><persName>Thomas P Hart</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr Stephen Austin</persName> <placeName>Texas</placeName>.</p>

        </div1>
    </body>
